<TITLE> 1 dies in clash with police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  One man was killed in a clash with police at Akhaura in Brahmanbaria early Tuesday. Thirty-year old Abu Salek was shot dead as police opened fire when a group of people attacked the Akhaura health complex at around 2am, said Osman Gani, additional superintendent of police. Four people, including a policeman, were also injured, he said. The people attacked the hospital following a clash between two groups of villagers, police and witnesses said. Police arrested Qaiyum Miah, who also had gunshot wounds. The injured policeman is Shafkul Islam, assistant sub-inspector of Akhaura police station. Two others, Nurul Islam and Abul Bashar, were admitted to the health complex. The people who attacked the health complex initially opened fire on the police when the law enforcers arrived at the scene to bring the situation under control, said Osman Gani. Police fired 16 rounds during the skirmish, he said. Two groups of people of Bautala village clashed on Monday. Several injured were admitted to the health complex. The group attacked the hospital attempting to snatch away the wounded rivals. As police went to the spot they opened fire, upon which the police retaliated. Additional policemen have been deployed around the health complex to avoid further untoward incident. bdnew
